  "summary": "TPC-H analytical workload dominated by large fact table scans (lineitem: 60M rows, orders: 15M) with selective filters (1-20% reduction), multi-way joins, and medium-cardinality aggregations. Q1 is the baseline heavy scan; Q3/Q18 involve complex join chains; Q9 has string filtering. Key optimization levers: (1) Parallel execution across 64 cores with morsel-driven scans; (2) Hash joins with proper join ordering; (3) Early filter pushdown (especially c_mktsegment, p_name LIKE, l_discount); (4) Zone map pruning on date/numeric columns; (5) Vectorized aggregation and SIMD-accelerated calculations for expressions like SUM(price × (1-discount))."
